Enclosing class:
Context
public static enum Context.ContextLabel
extends java.lang.Enum<Context.ContextLabel>

The context label describes through which component the context was created (i.e., the prior "where" field). We use the context label in some cases to identify triples with a certain property, e.g. triples created in the Wiki when updating semantic links. Therefore, do NOT change existing labels. Extension of this data structure should be unproblematic, though.
